{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/open-data-for-machine-learning-b5c6ef3f5a80", "time": 1682996709.773518, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/open-data-for-machine-learning-b5c6ef3f5a80/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Improving Machine Learning through Open Data | by Albert C. | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Improving Machine Learning through Open Data", "description": "Open Data is accepted as a practice of transparency and accountability by governments and institutions. In this article, we outline why Open Data can unlock the potential of actual Machine Learning"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://opendata-ajuntament.barcelona.cat/en/", "anchor_text": "OpenDataBcn", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://opendata.paris.fr/explore/?sort=modified", "anchor_text": "open data Paris", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://dati.comune.roma.it/", "anchor_text": "dati comune", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://daten.berlin.de/", "anchor_text": "aten.berlin", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://www.data.gouv.fr/fr/", "anchor_text": "data.gouv.fr", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "http://www.data.gov.my/", "anchor_text": "data.gov.my", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "http://datosabiertos.presidencia.go.cr/home", "anchor_text": "datosabiertos.presidencia.go.cr", "paragraph_index": 1}], "all_paragraphs": ["The P2P Foundation includes the definition of Open Data as the philosophy and practice requiring that certain data be freely available to everyone, without restrictions from copyright. patents or other mechanisms of control [2].", "In recent years as an exercise of transparency governments and city councils create open data portals where the authorities push a lot of data to be freely accessible to citizens. Cities like Barcelona (OpenDataBcn), Paris (open data Paris), Rome (dati comune) or Berlin (daten.berlin) have an Open Data Portal, changing the granularity to countries exist a portal for almost every country in the world: France (data.gouv.fr), Malasia (data.gov.my) or Costa Rica (datosabiertos.presidencia.go.cr).", "Nowadays is easy to find a dataset of almost everything, in a few clicks you can find, as for instance datasets related to territory (parking spaces of a city), population (Level of education), governance (electoral results)... The benefits of Open Data from an ethical movement essentially focus on empowering the resident with data that somehow can be used for his own profit. Clearly stated in the article \u201c5 benefits of open government data\u201d [3] we found:", "As Stated Before Open Data can unlock the potential of Machine Learning. The reason is simple including external data can help to enhance models, discovering new patterns and solving problems such as parity.", "**Corporate Data: that\u2019s how I refer to data owned by a project: like information of clients, consumption \u2026", "In order to include Open Data variables into an ML Algorithm, we need to include a Proxy between the raw data and the Input of the classifier. This proxy is responsible to transform and align data.", "Data must have same Granularity, all the dimensions must have the same periodicity. If we are predicting monthly weather, Open Data dimensions need to be also in months. Otherwise, it can induce bias in the model. The two sources of information need to be normalized (Rescaling, Mean normalization or Standardization are common techniques) and of course in the same unit, not try to make a model mixing data in kilometres and miles.", "Also is important to maintain an imbalanced proportion of dimensions. In most of the cases, the number of corporate dimensions needs to be larger than Open Data dimensions. The reason is simple guess we are predicting the stock market and 1 variable is the historical value (corporate data) of the stock and other 100 variables are from Open Data (GPD of the country, level of education or type of economic activities). In this case, most of the predictions will be build only with Open Data dimensions without using corporate data. For this reason, is essential to weight dimensions or limit its usage as auxiliary dimensions.", "Finally, actual Open Data Portals have barriers [4] to be adopted by third parties, governments should not limit on simply publish data. To enable reusability of this valuable information it needs to ensure the following features:", "Standard file format, the data is shared in different file formats (even you can find in files in pdf). The portals should work in establish a standard and share all the files in the same format (json and csv are prefered).", "Metadata, all datasets must be followed by a description of each variable (if it is tabular data row information). A good practice is using RDF, a standard created by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) which has features that facilitate data merging and support the evolution of schemas over time [5]", "Periodicity and consistency of data, The data should be updated periodically and keep a history of it. In the same way, the user must be informed of new versions of the data. The data also have to be consistent over time, the identifiers of the data not change over time.", "API access (Application Programming Interface), accessing and downloading data of the portal is a costly activity, for this reason, they have to enable an API to upgrade the data automatically", "To sum up, Open Data can unlock new potential in Artificial Intelligence projects and help to solve problems as parity. Furthermore, this combination is not a trivial task Open Data websites needs to ensure the reusability of the data and ML Engineers need to know how to merge this bunch of knowledge.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Fraud and Anomaly detection researcher applied to the cyber-security and energies sector (@albertcalv)"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fb5c6ef3f5a80&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fopen-data-for-machine-learning-b5c6ef3f5a80&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fopen-data-for-machine-learning-b5c6ef3f5a80&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fopen-data-for-machine-learning-b5c6ef3f5a80&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fopen-data-for-machine-learning-b5c6ef3f5a80&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/?source=post_page-----b5c6ef3f5a80--------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/?source=post_page-----b5c6ef3f5a80--------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Towards Data Science"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/@albertcalv?source=post_page--